AFTER 'BRUN PRINT ON'; YOU CAN USETHE  '&' TO TOGGLE THE PRINTER ONAND OFF.   (IT ALTERNATELY ISSUES'PR#1' AND 'PR#0'COMMANDS.)IN IMMEDIATE MODE; A SYNTAX ERROR ISREPORTED; BUT THE PRINTER IS STILLTOGGLED NONETHELESS.THE 80-COLUMN CARD MUST BE TURNEDOFF;  AND IT WON'T WORK IF ACARRIAGE RETURN  WASN'T THE LASTTHING PRINTED OUT;      SIMILAR TOTHE RULES FOR ISSUING DOSCOMMANDS BY PRECEDING THEM WITH ACARRIAGE RETURN AND THEN CTRL-D.